    "body": "@nickjm @bmaurer Apologies to both of you for misunderstanding what's happening here.\r\n\r\nPer Ben Burns' response to @nickjm this should be resolved in a Truffle patch release due tomorrow. Latest Ganache is now emulating the behavior of the main net clients in signaling error states via status field alone, rather than attaching an error object to the response which Web3 detects and throws on. The latest ganache release can be run with a flag that restores its old behavior (see the ganache release notes) although starting Thursday, truffle-contract will manage these errors correctly and be fully compatible with both Ganache and the main net clients.",
